The ATLAS detector [37] covers nearly the entire solid angle2 around the collision point. It consists of an inner tracking detector surrounded by a thin superconducting solenoid magnet producing a 2 T axial magnetic field, electromagnetic and hadronic calorimeters, and an external muon spectrometer incorporating three large toroid magnet assemblies. The inner detector consists of a high-granularity silicon pixel detector, including the newly installed insertable B-layer [38], and a silicon microstrip tracker, together providing precision tracking in the pseudorapidity range |η|<2.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
