				\begin{document}$$5\,\%$$\end{document}, affecting the overall normalisation of all processes estimated from the simulation. It is derived, following a methodology similar to that detailed in Ref. [94], from a calibration of the luminosity scale using x–y beam-separation scans performed in August 2015. The uncertainty associated with the modelling of pile-up arises mainly from differences between the expected and observed fraction of the visible pp cross section.

